/**
 * @file INSTALL
 * 
 * @brief Installation instructions
 *
 * <ol>
 *
 * <li>Run 'configure'.
 *
 * Use 'configure --help' to see all of the arguments configure
 * accepts. 
 *
 * <li>Run 'make'.
 *
 * You can change the compiler configure will use by setting CXX when
 * running configure. For example, to build using the C++ Sunpro compiler
\verbatim
configure CXX=CC
\endverbatim
 *
 * <li>Run 'make install'.
 *
 * After 'make install', the header files, libraries, and executables
 * can be found under the PREFIX directory (defined by --prefix=PREFIX
 * when running configure).
 *
 * <li> Set environment variables to find the library. If the library
 * is not installed in a system directory, set the environment
 * variables LD_LIBRARY_PATH (or its equivalent) accordingly. You will
 * probably want to do this in your .bashrc or .cshrc file or a file
 * that is included by them so that these are set automatically every
 * time you log in.
 *
 * <li> bash shell users
 *
\verbatim
export EQSIMIO_DIR=/home/johndoe/eqsimio
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}:${EQSIMIO_DIR}/lib
\endverbatim
 *
 * <li> tcsh shell users
\verbatim
setenv EQSIMIO_DIR /home/johndoe/eqsimio
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH ${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}:${EQSIMIO_DIR}/lib
\endverbatim
 *
 * </ol>
 *
 * @section knownissues Known Issues
 *
 * None at this time.
 *
 */

